  </study_design_info>
  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Global and regional cerebral blood flow</measure>
    <time_frame>Within 15 minutes of intervention initiation</time_frame>
    <description>Cerebral blood flow will be measured by the arterial spin labeling technique (ASL) which provides information expressed in mL/100g/min. Using 3-T MRI technology,we will first acquire T1 images of the brain and sub-regions of interest. Thereafter, ASL sequences will be acquired in contiguous slices. The procedure will be followed on sedation and off sedation for healthy volunteers (in random order) and at mean arterial pressure of 65 mmHg and 75 mmHg (in random order) in patients receiving vasopressor therapy.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
